{"id":103261,"date":"2024-03-26T14:05:47","date_gmt":"2024-03-26T14:05:47","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/spines.com\/?post_type=docs&#038;p=103261"},"modified":"2024-03-26T15:19:09","modified_gmt":"2024-03-26T15:19:09","password":"","slug":"formating-faq","status":"publish","type":"docs","link":"https:\/\/spines.com\/docs\/formating-faq\/","title":{"rendered":"FAQ"},"content":{"rendered":"<div\n\tclass=\"betterdocs-faq-wrapper layout-modern icon-after  betterdocs-shortcode\">\n\t<h2 class=\" betterdocs-faq-section-title\"><\/h2>\n\t<div class=\"betterdocs-faq-inner-wrapper\">\n\t\t<div class=\"betterdocs-faq-title\">\n\t<h3 class=\"betterdocs-faq-title-tag\">Formatting FAQs<\/h3><\/div>\n<ul class=\"betterdocs-faq-list\"><li><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-group\"><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-post\">\n\t\t<p class=\"betterdocs-faq-post-name\">\n\t\tHow do I start formatting my book?\t<\/p>\n\t<svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconminus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"stroke-width=\"2\"><g fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconplus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><g stroke-width=\"2\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"square\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\"><path d=\"M12 7v10M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><\/div>\n<div class=\"betterdocs-faq-main-content\" >\n\t<p>Begin by choosing the type of the first paragraph for your book. Select the option that best appeals to you and click &#8216;Next&#8217; to proceed with the formatting process.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/li><li><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-group\"><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-post\">\n\t\t<p class=\"betterdocs-faq-post-name\">\n\t\tWhat formatting options are available for my book?\t<\/p>\n\t<svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconminus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"stroke-width=\"2\"><g fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconplus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><g stroke-width=\"2\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"square\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\"><path d=\"M12 7v10M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><\/div>\n<div class=\"betterdocs-faq-main-content\" >\n\t<p>You have several formatting options, including choosing indentation for each chapter, adding a table of contents, clarifying the fictional nature of your content, and optionally including an age restriction declaration.<\/p><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/li><li><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-group\"><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-post\">\n\t\t<p class=\"betterdocs-faq-post-name\">\n\t\tHow can I ensure each chapter starts with indentation?\t<\/p>\n\t<svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconminus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"stroke-width=\"2\"><g fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconplus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><g stroke-width=\"2\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"square\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\"><path d=\"M12 7v10M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><\/div>\n<div class=\"betterdocs-faq-main-content\" >\n\t<p>During the formatting styles selection step, you can select the checkbox that aligns with your preference to ensure that each chapter starts with indentation.<\/p><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/li><li><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-group\"><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-post\">\n\t\t<p class=\"betterdocs-faq-post-name\">\n\t\tIs it possible to add a table of contents for easy navigation?\t<\/p>\n\t<svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconminus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"stroke-width=\"2\"><g fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconplus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><g stroke-width=\"2\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"square\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\"><path d=\"M12 7v10M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><\/div>\n<div class=\"betterdocs-faq-main-content\" >\n\t<p>Yes, you can select the option to add a table of contents during the formatting styles selection step, which helps in easy navigation through the book.<\/p><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/li><li><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-group\"><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-post\">\n\t\t<p class=\"betterdocs-faq-post-name\">\n\t\tHow do I declare that the content in my book is fictional?\t<\/p>\n\t<svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconminus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"stroke-width=\"2\"><g fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconplus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><g stroke-width=\"2\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"square\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\"><path d=\"M12 7v10M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><\/div>\n<div class=\"betterdocs-faq-main-content\" >\n\t<p>You can include a statement during the formatting styles selection step that clarifies the story, characters, and places in the book are fictional.<\/p><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/li><li><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-group\"><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-post\">\n\t\t<p class=\"betterdocs-faq-post-name\">\n\t\tCan I include an age restriction declaration in my book?\t<\/p>\n\t<svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconminus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"stroke-width=\"2\"><g fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconplus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><g stroke-width=\"2\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"square\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\"><path d=\"M12 7v10M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><\/div>\n<div class=\"betterdocs-faq-main-content\" >\n\t<p>Yes, there is an option to include an age restriction declaration in your book. This can be selected during the formatting styles selection step if required.<\/p><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/li><li><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-group\"><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-post\">\n\t\t<p class=\"betterdocs-faq-post-name\">\n\t\tHow do I acknowledge contributors in my book?\t<\/p>\n\t<svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconminus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"stroke-width=\"2\"><g fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconplus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><g stroke-width=\"2\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"square\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\"><path d=\"M12 7v10M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><\/div>\n<div class=\"betterdocs-faq-main-content\" >\n\t<p>In the adding contributors step, you can acknowledge all individuals who made significant contributions to your book, such as co-authors, editors, illustrators, translators, and designers, by including their names and contributions.<\/p><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/li><li><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-group\"><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-post\">\n\t\t<p class=\"betterdocs-faq-post-name\">\n\t\tWhat happens after I add all the necessary contributors?\t<\/p>\n\t<svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconminus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"stroke-width=\"2\"><g fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconplus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><g stroke-width=\"2\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"square\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\"><path d=\"M12 7v10M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><\/div>\n<div class=\"betterdocs-faq-main-content\" >\n\t<p>Once you&#8217;ve added all the necessary contributors, you can complete the formatting section by clicking &#8216;Finish&#8217;. This concludes the formatting process for your book.<\/p><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/li><li><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-group\"><div class=\"betterdocs-faq-post\">\n\t\t<p class=\"betterdocs-faq-post-name\">\n\t\tWhat should I do if I need to format my book in a specific way not covered in the options?\t<\/p>\n\t<svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconminus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"stroke-width=\"2\"><g fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><svg class=\"betterdocs-faq-iconplus\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><g stroke-width=\"2\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#528ffe\" stroke-linecap=\"square\" stroke-miterlimit=\"10\"><path d=\"M12 7v10M17 12H7\"><\/path><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"11\"><\/circle><\/g><\/svg><\/div>\n<div class=\"betterdocs-faq-main-content\" >\n\t<p>While the tutorial covers basic formatting options, for specific formatting needs not directly addressed, consider exploring advanced settings or consulting with a professional formatter for custom requests.<\/p>\n<\/p>\n<\/p><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/li><\/ul>\t<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":4845,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"doc_category":[199],"doc_tag":[],"class_list":["post-103261","docs","type-docs","status-publish","hentry","doc_category-formatting"],"acf":[],"year_month":"2026-02","word_count":8,"total_views":"1180","reactions":{"happy":"2","normal":"0","sad":"1"},"author_info":{"name":"Itamar Asulin","author_nicename":"itamarspines-com","author_url":"https:\/\/spines.com\/author\/itamarspines-com\/"},"doc_category_info":[{"term_name":"Formatting","term_url":"https:\/\/spines.com\/docs-category\/formatting\/"}],"doc_tag_info":[],"knowledge_base_info":[],"knowledge_base_slug":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/spines.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/docs\/103261","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/spines.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/docs"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/spines.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/docs"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/spines.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/4845"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/spines.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=103261"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/spines.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/docs\/103261\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/spines.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/m